2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
1 tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
4 tbsp Italian Breadcrumbs
1 unit(s) Lemon
113 g Baby Tomatoes
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
56 g Baby Spinach
½ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1.5 tbsp Oil*

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
Save breadcrumbs and Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend for another use. Reserve all the feta to serve in step 6.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil, then Beyond Meat® patties. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, cook patties in 2 batches, using 1/2 tbsp oil per batch.)
Pan-fry until golden-brown, 2-3 min per side.
Meanwhile, core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch slices.
Add peppers, Zesty Garlic Blend and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to one side of a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with pepper, then toss to coat. Set aside.

Transfer seared Beyond Meat® patties to the other side of the baking sheet with peppers.
Roast in the middle of the oven until peppers are tender and patties are cooked through, 10-12 min.**

Meanwhile, zest, then juice half the lemon. Cut remaining lemon into wedges.
Halve tomatoes.
Add mayo, lemon zest and 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) lemon juice to a small bowl.
Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) lemon juice and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine. (TIP: Add a pinch of sugar to dressing, if desired.)
Add tomatoes and spinach, then toss to combine.

Divide Beyond Meat® patties, peppers and salad between plates.
Sprinkle remaining feta over salad.
Squeeze a lemon wedge over top, if desired.
Serve lemony mayo alongside for dipping.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, skip the instructions to form the patties. Save breadcrumbs and Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend for another use. Use all the Zesty garlic blend to season peppers. Reserve all the feta to serve in step 6.

Sear and cook Beyond Meat® patties the same way the recipe instructs you to sear and cook the beef.